{
  "stem": "2004.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Hungarians grabbed part of Czechoslovakia which was known as Podkarpatska Rus.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Poles grabbed the part that was known as Zaolzie, which sort of-- that's finished up the Czech Republic at the time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Which was sad because out of the Eastern European countries, I think their democracy was probably the best functioned democracy.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They really were.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was a pity to see a Czech Republic being swallowed up by three neighbors, so to say.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we just wondered how long it'll be before the Germans will swallow up Poland altogether.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Which as history, as it turns out in retrospect, it didn't take very long.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It took an extra year or so, and they swallowed up Poland, and then, later on the rest of Europe.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Typical Shabbat, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We always went to shul on Friday.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At least, I went with my father to shul on Friday night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course, we walked because we didn't have a car.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Very few people in our town had cars.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after services-- by the way, for Friday night, we went to our-- we did not go to the shul on the Czech side.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But on our street there was a shul, which even though we belonged for the-- for any holiday we went to the Czech side, because that's where my grandfather was the official in there.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was the gabbai.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We went to a temple, to a shul, on our street which we were members as well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And after that, after usually-- there was usually the traditional Shabbos dinner.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And obviously, nobody went to work on Shabbat morning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the Shabbat dinner was a traditional type, with fish, and soup, and challah, and boiled chicken, and, and boiled fruit, dessert, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
